    {"repo": "github.com/etcd-io/raft", "path": "raft/log.go", "symbol": "snapshot"},
    {"repo": "github.com/etcd-io/raft", "path": "raft/raft.go", "symbol": "maybeSendAppend"}
  ],
  "text": "ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable is defined in github.com/etcd-io/raft (raft/storage.go, line 38) as a sentinel error returned by the Storage interface when a required snapshot is temporarily unavailable. The error signals that the Raft state machine should retry later.\n\nDuring node rejoin for log catch-up, the snapshot availability check follows this chain:\n\n1. **Definition (raft/storage.go:38)**: ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable is defined as part of the Storage interface contract for the Snapshot() method. Custom Storage implementations (e.g., with async snapshot generation) return this error to indicate the snapshot is not yet ready.\n\n2. **Snapshot Retrieval (raft/log.go)**: The raftLog.snapshot() method checks for unstable snapshots first, then delegates to storage.Snapshot(). This is called when the leader needs to send a snapshot to a lagging follower.\n\n3. **Availability Check During Log Catch-Up (raft/raft.go - maybeSendAppend() function, lines ~469-474)**: When a rejoining node is too far behind and required log entries are compacted away, the leader attempts to send a snapshot. If storage.Snapshot() returns ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable, the leader logs a debug message and returns false without sending a message. This silently bails out, and the Raft heartbeat/tick cycle will retry on the next tick.\n\n4. **Progress State Management (raft/tracker/progress.go)**: When a snapshot is successfully retrieved and sent, the follower's progress transitions via BecomeSnapshot(sindex), setting the state to StateSnapshot.\n\n5. **Pausing Replication (raft/tracker/state.go)**: While in StateSnapshot, IsPaused() returns true, halting all further replication to that peer until the snapshot transfer completes.\n\nThe flow handles the specific scenario: when an etcd node fails to rejoin a cluster with 'ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable', it means the cluster leader attempted to catch the rejoining node up via snapshot, but the snapshot was not immediately available. The Raft protocol gracefully handles this by retrying on subsequent ticks until the snapshot becomes available."
}

